article.description: — Deon Stroud had a career-high 22 points as Fresno State got past San Jose State 80-65 on Sunday.
article.headline: Stroud leads Fresno St. past San Jose St. 80-65
article.linkText: Stroud leads Fresno St. past San Jose St. 80-65
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. -- — Deon Stroud had a career-high 22 points as Fresno State got past San Jose State 80-65 on Sunday. Stroud made 5 of 6 3-pointers. Jordan Campbell had 16 points and nine rebounds for Fresno State (5-3, 3-3 Mountain West Conference). Orlando Robinson added 11 points, seven rebounds and six assists. Richard Washington had 24 points and eight rebounds for the Spartans (2-8, 0-6). Ralph Agee added 14 points. Nate Lacewell had 10 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
